claim.claim-text:
34. A method for production of a polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) and ethanol comprising: 
culturing a transgenic yeast cell comprising a first nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a PHA polymerase and at least one second nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence selected from the group consisting of a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding an acetoacetyl-CoA reductase and a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a &bgr;-ketothiolase under conditions to cause the production of ethanol; 
isolating the ethanol from the cell culture; 
culturing the yeast cell under conditions to cause the production of PHA; and 
isolating the PHA from the yeast cell.

51. A method for production of a polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) and lactic acid comprising: 
culturing a transgenic yeast cell comprising a first nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a PHA polymerase and at least one second nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence selected from the group consisting of a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding an acetoacetyl-CoA reductase and a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a &bgr;-ketothiolase under conditions to cause the production of lactic acid; 
isolating the lactic acid from the cell culture; 
culturing the yeast cell under conditions to cause the production of PHA; and 
isolating the PHA from the yeast cell.

68. A method for production of a polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) and ethanol in a transgenic bacterial cell comprising: 
providing a transgenic bacterial cell comprising a first nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a PHA polymerase and at least one second nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence selected from the group consisting of a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding an acetoacetyl-CoA reductase and a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a &bgr;-ketothiolase; 
culturing the bacterial cell under conditions to cause the production of ethanol; 
isolating the ethanol from the cell culture; 
culturing the bacterial cell under conditions to cause the production of PHA; and 
isolating the PHA from the bacterial cell.

82. A method for production of a polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) and ethanol in a transgenic E. coli cell comprising: 
providing a transgenic E. coli cell comprising a first nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a PHA polymerase and at least one second nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence selected from the group consisting of a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding an acetoacetyl-CoA reductase and a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a &bgr;-ketothiolase; 
culturing the E. coli cell under conditions to cause the production of ethanol; 
isolating the ethanol from the cell culture; 
culturing the E. coli cell under conditions to cause the production of PHA; and 
isolating the PHA from the E. coli cell.

84. A method for production of a polyhydroxyalkanoate (PHA) and lactic acid comprising: 
providing a transgenic bacterial cell comprising a first nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a PHA polymerase and at least one second nucleic acid fragment comprising a heterologous nucleotide sequence selected from the group consisting of a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding an acetoacetyl-CoA reductase and a heterologous nucleotide sequence encoding a &bgr;-ketothiolase; 
culturing the bacterial cell under conditions to cause the production of lactic acid; 
isolating the lactic acid from the cell culture; 
culturing the bacterial cell under conditions to cause the production of PHA; and 
isolating the PHA from the bacterial cell.
